parameters.name: RADIATION_COUNTS
parameters.description: The calibrated, shutter compensated, radiation count. The count values are calibrated to counts as reaching the CCD per image cycle (250ms).

parameters.name: BBO_FLAG
parameters.description: Indicating presence of a bright luminous object in the field of view at the time of acquisition 0 means no BBO, 1 means at least one BBO.

parameters.name: OBJECT_COUNT
parameters.description: Number of stellar candidate objects identified in the image

parameters.name: SHUTTER_COMPENSATION
parameters.description: The measured count depends on the use of electronic shutter. This field indicates the level of compensation applied for the engineering count values

parameters.name: RADIATION_COUNT_RAW
parameters.description: The raw radiation count as telemetered by the instrument

parameters.name: UTC_TIME
parameters.description: The UTC time in decimal seconds. The time epoch is seconds since Jan 1st, 2000 at noon.

parameters.name: OMNI-DIRECTIONAL FLUX
parameters.description: The external omnidirectional flux in [particles/cm^2/s], within the energy sensitivity range of the sensor.
